{[%evp 0,37,27,30,27,-11,-2,6,29,34,44,28,28,21,32,34,33,2,30,30,35,21,23,27,27,35,35,35,30,42,66,75,75,64,72,39,50,49,47,38]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Qe7 5. g3 Nc6 {[%csl Gb1,Yd7][%cal Yd7d5,Yb1d2,Yb1a3]} 6. e3 O-O (6... Bxd2+ 7. Qxd2 d6 {It doesn't make a difference if Black plays this plan without castling.} 8. Nc3 e5 9. Bg2 {There is nothing better than castle.} O-O (9... e4 $6 {was tried in the game Davtyan-Gholami, 2019, but it is not a great move.} 10. Ng1 {is strong enough.} d5 $6 {was played, but it is even worse.} (10... O-O 11. Nge2 $16 {[%cal Gh2h3,Gg3g4,Ge2g3] Worse position strategically for Black.}) 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 12. cxd5 Nb4 13. d6 $1 {Strong move.} Qxd6 14. Bxe4 $16 {Extra pawn, without any compensation, White won.}) 10. O-O {Transposes to 6...0-0.}) 7. Bg2 Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2 d6 9. Nc3 e5 {This is the starting position.} 10. O-O {My main recommendation, because anyway this position can be achieved from many move orders, so better to know it.} (10. Nd5 {has also been tried and it is a good option.} Qd8 $1 {But this is a strong move.} (10... Nxd5 {If Black takes, White has chances for an advantage.} 11. cxd5 Nd8 {The best moves:} (11... Nb8 {was tried in Sonis-Tregubov, but Black is just worse.} 12. dxe5 (12. Qc3 {was played in the game, but the position is unclear after} e4 13. Nd2 f5 $13) 12... dxe5 13. e4 Nd7 14. O-O Nf6 15. Rfe1 {Long term better for White.} Bg4 16. Rac1 Rfc8 17. h3 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 Ne8 19. Qe3 Nd6 20. Bg4 $16 {Just worse for Black.}) 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. O-O f6 14. Rfd1 $36 {Some chances to be better exist, it's not completely equal.}) 11. O-O e4 {The best engine move.} (11... Bg4 {Girya-Vasilevich.} 12. h3 (12. b4 $5 {deserves attention.}) 12... Bxf3 13. Bxf3 exd4 {was played in the game.} 14. exd4 Nxd5 15. Bxd5 Qf6 16. Rad1 Rae8 17. Kg2 $14 {[%cal Gb2b4,Gb4b5] Long term pressure for White.}) (11... Re8 {Possible move.} 12. Qc3 {is the best, played in the game Eljanov-Ivanchuk, 2014.} (12. dxe5 {was played in the game Barp-Manca, 2021, but the position is empty after} dxe5 13. Rad1 e4 $1 {Strong move.} 14. Ng5 Bf5 15. Qc3 {Black took on d5, but} h6 $146 {was stronger.} 16. Nxf6+ Qxf6 17. Qxf6 gxf6 18. Nh3 Bg4 $11 {The endgame is just equal. Black has a bad structure, but very active pieces.}) 12... Ne4 {Ivanchuk played this, but the knight is misplaced.} (12... exd4 $6 {Just bad positionally.} 13. Nxd4 $16 {White is better.}) (12... a5 $5 {Maybe Black can play a waiting move like this, and at this point you can take on e5.} 13. dxe5 Nxe5 (13... dxe5 14. Rad1 {Because here e4 is another story.} e4 15. Ng5 $16 {[%csl Re4] Problems with the e4 pawn.}) 14. Nd4 $14 {But you don't have to exchange, and it is slightly better for White.} (14. Nxe5 {This is closer to equality, because} dxe5 $11 {[%csl Gc6][%cal Gc7c6] Once the knights are exchanged, c6 is possible.})) 13. Qd3 $5 $146 {was even more precise, because it defends d4.} (13. Qc2 exd4 14. exd4 Bg4 15. Rad1 Nf6 {is how the game continued and after} 16. Ne3 $5 $14 {White has a small advantage.}) 13... exd4 14. Nxd4 {White can take with the knight.} Nc5 15. Qd2 Nxd4 16. exd4 Ne4 17. Qf4 Nf6 18. Rfe1 $14 {With initiative on the e-file.}) 12. Ng5 {is critical.} Nxd5 13. cxd5 Ne7 (13... Qxg5 {Black is worse after} 14. dxc6 Qd5 15. cxb7 Bxb7 16. Qc2 $14 {Play on the c-file.}) 14. Nxe4 Nxd5 {New position, maybe White's only interesting plan is to play} 15. f4 $5 {[%cal Gf4f5] With idea of f5.} f5 $1 {Strong move.} (15... c6 16. f5 $14 {could be better for White.}) 16. Ng5 c6 {If c6, we can play for the structure:} 17. Bxd5+ cxd5 18. Qg2 Qa5 19. a4 h6 20. b4 {This is playable, but also Black has compensation after:} Qc7 21. Qxd5+ Kh8 22. Nf3 Qe7 23. Qb3 Bd7 24. Kf2 $44 {More or less playable position.}) 10... e4 {is a serious move. And now engine is convinced that White's best move is 11.Ng5.} (10... exd4 $2 {is a bad positional move, and it was played against me by Jospem.} 11. Nxd4 Ne5 12. b3 c6 {And here obviously White is better, but I didn't play the most precise move.} 13. h3 {It's a bit slow, but also good enough.} (13. e4 $16 {is the easiest.}) 13... Re8 {was played and the game later finished in a draw, but now} (13... c5 $5 $146 {is an idea here, but White has the objective advantage also here after} 14. Ndb5 Bxh3 $1 15. f4 $1 Bxg2 16. fxe5 Bxf1 17. exf6 $14 {Still advantage, but more complicated.}) 14. f4 $5 $16 {would have lead to a big advantage.}) (10... Bg4 {Should be mentioned, because it was played against me by the young GM Subelj.} 11. b3 $146 {is a good move instead, to support the c4 pawn.} (11. h3 $6 {I went for the natural move, but suddenly after} Bxf3 12. Bxf3 exd4 {Black has a trick!} 13. exd4 Qe6 $1 {[%csl Rc4,Rh3] 2 pawns are attacked.} 14. Nd5 {Still, I am not worse, and the game soon ended in a draw after} (14. d5 {is met with} Ne5 $1 $132 {[%cal Rd5e6,Ge5f3] That is the point.}) 14... Nxd5 15. cxd5 Qf6 $1 16. dxc6 Qxf3 17. cxb7 Qxb7 18. Rac1 $11 {It was a morning round, so definitely it took me by surprise his preparation.}) 11... Rfe8 (11... Qd7 {If Black stops h3, the endgame can be quite dangerous after} 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Qxd7 Bxd7 14. Rfd1 $14 {[%cal Gf3g5,Gg5e4,Gc3b5,Gc3d5,Gh2h3,Yg3g4] A lot of pressure and very flexible pieces.}) (11... e4 12. Ng5 Bf5 {It's the same as 10...e4, just with the extra move b3, so it cannot be bad for White.}) 12. h3 {Now there is no more trick.} Bxf3 13. Bxf3 exd4 14. exd4 Qe6 15. Kg2 $16 {[%csl Gc4][%cal Gb3c4] But we can defend h3, and c4 is protected.} (15. d5 {Not this, because still} Ne5 $1 $132 {is strong.})) (10... Re8 {is a normal useful move.} 11. h3 $5 {Useful move, stopping Bg4.} (11. b3 {was played in the game Barp-Grigorov, 2022. It's a possible move.} Bg4 12. h3 Bf5 13. Nd5 {is probably a better move, and after} (13. Nh4 {was how the game continued, and it is a bit strange.} Bd7 14. d5 $13 {In the end, White lost.}) 13... Qd8 14. dxe5 dxe5 15. Rfd1 $36 {Some pressure exists.}) (11. Nd5 $5 {We can go for this plan now.} Qd8 12. Qc3 {Transposes to 10.Nd5.}) 11... a5 12. Qc2 {Now Black can take} exd4 {[%csl Rc2,Gd2] Saying that we cannot play for the good structure anymore.} 13. exd4 {But this structure is also good for White.} Bd7 14. Rae1 Qd8 (14... Qf8 $2 {allows} 15. Nd5 $1 $16 {[%csl Rc7] And the pawn is lost.}) 15. Rxe8+ {Now a concrete reaction:} Qxe8 16. Nd5 Qd8 17. Ng5 $40 {looks very interesting.}) 11. Ng5 $1 {More concrete move, but objectively stronger.} (11. Ne1 {But a few years ago, this was also considered interesting. There are two games here: one of mine, against Sousa, and Anand - Kollars, 2016.} Bf5 12. Nc2 a6 {Engine suggestion.} (12... a5 {was played by Kollars, but maybe it is not the best.} 13. a3 {Anand played a3, with idea of b4 and after} a4 14. Nb4 $1 {was his idea, and very quickly, White got a much better position.} Qd7 15. Qc2 Nxb4 16. axb4 Qc6 17. c5 b5 18. cxb6 Qxb6 19. Rxa4 $16 {Just extra pawn, Anand converted in the end.}) (12... Rac8 {I followed the preparation of Anand, and after} 13. b4 $36 {I managed to win the game, the positions are playable, but engine says that it's not so bad for Black.}) 13. b4 Rfe8 14. a4 Qd7 15. a5 (15. b5 {If you push, after} Na5 $132 {[%csl Rc4] Some problems with the c4 pawn.}) 15... d5 $1 16. cxd5 Ne7 $132 {And engine is not impressed.}) 11... Bf5 12. f3 $1 {Very important move.} (12. h4 $6 {was played by Deac against Ferreira, but it is a bad move.} h6 $1 $146 {And the knight is misplaced after} 13. Nh3 Qd7 14. Nf4 Ne7 $132 {[%cal Gc7c6,Gg7g5] Black has easy play.}) 12... exf3 {has to be played.} 13. Rxf3 $1 {The best recapture.} Bg6 14. Raf1 h6 {is the critical move, and now we play:} (14... Nd7 {[%csl Gc3,Ye4] was played in the game Krysa-Panelo, and here a good maneuver is} 15. Nh3 $1 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gh3f4,Gf4d5] The knight goes to d5.} Rae8 16. Nf4 Nb6 17. b3 $16 {[%cal Gh2h4,Gh4h5] Just clear advantage for White.}) (14... Ng4 $5 $146 {[%csl Rg5] is maybe more useful than the knight on d7, because it attacks g5, but also potentially e3.} 15. Nh3 Rae8 {[%csl Re3] The pawn on e3 is attacked, so no time for Nf4.} 16. Re1 $5 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Gh3f4] is a better move probably, with the idea of Nf4-Nd5.} (16. e4 {is very natural, but the game is complicated after} Qd7 17. Nf4 Bxe4 18. Nxe4 Rxe4 {White has compensation, but the position is a mess, for example:} 19. Rb3 $1 {[%cal Re4d4,Gg2c6]} Ree8 20. h3 Nf6 21. Rxb7 $13 {More pleasant for White, but almost nothing.}) 16... Nd8 {[%cal Gc7c6] Natural plan.} 17. Nf4 c6 18. e4 {Now we can play e4.} Ne6 19. h3 Nf6 20. Rfe3 $14 {Of course, not a winning advantage, but definitely better, engine says +0.50.}) 15. Rxf6 $1 {The rook cannot be captured.} hxg5 {has to be played.} (15... gxf6 $2 {is just game over after} 16. Nge4 f5 17. Nd5 {White is simply winning.} Qd8 18. Nef6+ Kg7 19. e4 $18) 16. R6f2 {Best square.} Rae8 {We are following the game Barp-Karthikeyan, 2021.} 17. e4 $1 {[%cal Gg2f3,Gh2h4,Gg3h4,Gh4h5,Gf2g2] Important improvement.} (17. Re1 $6 {was played in the game, but it's a very slow move.} Qd7 18. e4 f6 $11 {[%cal Gc6d8,Gd8f7] It looks more pleasant for White, but in reality it's 0.00. It's nothing for White.}) 17... Qd8 {Engine suggests this as the best move.} (17... f6 {Here also} 18. h4 $1 {is the best plan.} gxh4 19. gxh4 $40 {[%cal Gg2f3,Gf2g2]}) (17... Qd7 {If the queen leaves the diagonal, White can play} 18. h4 $5 {Very interesting.} gxh4 19. gxh4 $36 {[%cal Gg2f3,Gf2g2,Gh4h5] Advantage for White.}) 18. Bf3 {But we wait for a move like} f6 {Where} (18... Qf6 {is how engine is playing it, but it is very strange.} 19. Rd1 Qd8 {We can improve slowly.} 20. h3 $40 {[%cal Gf2h2,Gh3h4] Important plan to remember, Black is suffering.}) 19. h4 $40 {The h4 plan is possible, with huge attack.} *

